'''''Out of the Ruins''''' is a [[lost film|lost]] 1928 silent film drama produced and distributed by [[First National Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.8080/default.html |work=[[The Library of Congress]] |title=American Silent Feature Film Survival Archive: ''Out of the Ruins'' |access-date=19 March 2019 |date=5 January 2017 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20140715032326/http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.8080/default.html |archive-date=15 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.silentsaregolden.com/arnefirstnational.html |title=The Lost Films of First National Pictures |work=Arne Andersen's Lost Film Files |access-date=19 March 2019}}</ref> [[John Francis Dillon (director)|John Francis Dillon]] directed and [[Richard Barthelmess]] stars.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/AbbrView.aspx?s=&Movie=11195 |title=The AFI Catalog of Feature Films: ''Out of the Ruins'' |access-date=19 March 2019 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20170620004602/http://www.afi.com/members//catalog/AbbrView.aspx?s=&Movie=11195 |archive-date=20 June 2017 |work=[[American Film Institute]]}}</ref>

==Cast==
*[[Richard Barthelmess]] - Lt. Pierre Dumont
*[[Robert Frazer]] - Paul Gilbert
*[[Marian Nixon]] - Yvonne Gilbert
*[[Emile Chautard]] - Pere Gilbert
*[[Bodil Rosing]] - Mere Gilbert
*[[Eugene Pallette]] - Volange
*[[Rose Dione]] - Mere Gourdain

